  <title>Define a snippet</title>

  <p>On the layouts shipping by default with <app>Onboard</app>, there are <key>buttons</key> that the user can associate with a custom defined text. These custom defined texts are called <em>snippets</em> in <app>Onboard</app> and the interface to define them is located in the Preferences dialog.</p>

  <p>To define a new <em>snippet</em> and give it a name, you can do the following:</p>
  <steps>
    <item><p>Open the <app>Preferences</app> dialog by using its <gui>desktop icon</gui>, the corresponding <key>button</key> in one of <app>Onboard</app>'s key layers or by choosing the appropriate <gui>menu</gui> in the <gui>indicator icon</gui>.</p></item>
    <item><p>Select the <gui>Snippets</gui> tab by clicking on it.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click on the <key>Add</key> button to add a new <em>snippet</em> definition or click on the <key>Remove</key> button to delete the selected <em>snippet</em>.</p></item>
    <item><p>Double click in the <gui>label</gui> or <gui>text</gui> column of the <em>snippet</em> to edit, in order to change its name or the text that it automatically writes.</p></item>
  </steps>

  <note><p>There is also a more direct way to define a <em>snippet</em>: simply perform a <key>left mouse button</key> click and hold on a <key>snippet button</key> and a little <gui>dialog</gui> will appear to define title and text of that <em>snippet</em>.</p></note>

  <p>For information about how to use a <em>snippet</em>, please have a look at the <link xref="snippet-usage" /> page.</p>

